cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a novel multichannel network with infrastructure support and analyzes its capacity and delay. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the capacity of the proposed network and uses information theory concepts to derive the capacity bounds.
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with a network of multiple agents (nodes) and their interactions, which falls under the scope of multiagent systems.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses a distributed network and its performance, which falls under the scope of distributed computing.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a network with infrastructure support, which involves control and management of the network, falling under the scope of systems and control.
